Comment: Good One

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: It's a bit long for a CoC. I suggest to skip the upper case condition, or one of the tests

✅ Approved the contribution.
Comment: waiting for this in coc ;

Goal
* Please do not format the example IP address as a [[variable]]. Hence, please change '[["10.25.210.27"]]' to 'e.g. {{10.25.210.27}}' (adding "e.g." and removing the double quotation marks at the same time).

* Please change "Hexadecimal" to "hexadecimal".

* Please add "The output of the hexadecimal numbers has to be in uppercase."

* Please add "Make sure to check that only numbers are admitted on each field."

(Note that "admited" should be spelled "admitted".)

Input
* Please delete '"10.25.210.20", make sure to check that only numbers are admited on each field'.

(No example required in Input section as that's shown in Example section. The other sentence should be moved to Goal section as it's nothing to do with input description.)

Output
* Please change "HEX (hexadecimal)" to "hexadecimal".

* Please change 'format: Input:"10.25.210.20" Output:{0x0A, 0x19, 0xD2, 0x14}' to "as described in the statement".

* Please change 'throw an error; Input:{"1023.2125.11210.6620", "10.21.20.60.10.20","n3s.aef.h4a1.a34"} Output:' to 'output the error'.

Constraints
* Please delete both constraints. Constraints impose a restriction on what cases the player should get, e.g. length of input, instead of repeating or adding the rules/logic that the player should include in their code.

Cases
* Each pair of test and validator should be similar but **different**. Please revise the cases.

Thanks.
